readiness.insight: Based on your moderately active lifestyle and recent VO2 Max reading of 33.4 ml/kg/min, you are somewhat prepared for climbing Freel Peak, but there are areas for improvement. Freel Peak is a difficult climb with a rating of 72 out of 100. To better prepare, consider incorporating more vigorous walking or running into your routine, aiming for at least 3-4 times a week. Gradually increase your activity intensity and duration to build endurance. Also, ensure you maintain a balanced diet rich in carbohydrates, proteins, and healthy fats to support your training. Stay hydrated and consider acclimatization techniques if you plan to summit, especially given the peak's high elevation of 3,318 meters.
